I have REALLY been enjoying my winter with @theericoakley. Even though we’ve just been been at home now for quite awhile, we’ve gotten so much done and have entered a new chapter I think for both of us. The “offseason” is so interesting. It’s such a different way to live than “traditional lives”. I truly don’t miss constantly being on tour and having only 3 months to get your $&@! together. Though I’m still subject to it a in some form since I only have Eric home for these 3 months, but we always make the best of it. 
This year it feels like growth. It feels like progress and re-shaping our lives into what we are really dreaming for. It means changes and uncomfortable and a LOT of talking. 
I’m so thankful to have someone so open and willing and accepting to work through life with.
Changes are happening. They might be scary sometimes but fear keeps us from doing things we would love to do, and I’m not about that. Bring on the unknown, the difficult, the confusing, that’s how we grow.

A LOT has changed for me. It likely comes at little surprise but I have decided to step down from my sponsorship with Dynamic Discs for 2023. I’ve spent 6 years on team Dynamic Discs. That’s a huge chunk of my life. I am so thankful for all the experiences and support I received over those years. I’ve grown as a person, a player, a representative and in so many unexpected ways as a media and video guru. They gave me so many opportunities when my life situation changed, when my interests changed, when I was injured. I look back on those years, and especially the early ones with so much joy and appreciation.
Obviously being off tour, my life has changed dramatically in the last 3 years. I needed ground under my feet, I needed a home base and stability and I needed a change to fulfil other pieces of my desires for life.
SO I’m exploring new avenues with Sun + Soil with plants and pottery, as well as travel and focusing on Whale Sacs, it is time for a change, and to remove that guilt of not playing often enough, not being involved enough, etc. my personal growth is on a rampage (in the best way possible) and for now that means stepping away from Dynamic.
I still play disc golf, quite a bit and with even more enjoyment and I’ll always be involved in the sport both with my business and my play.
Can’t wait for new opportunities ahead. #discgolf #dynamicdiscs

Date night! I’m SO sad Eric is leaving for tour in a week. 😭😭😭 I’m usually ready to have the house back to myself but that is absolutely not the case this year. We’ve been through so much together this off-season. Lots of good, loads of bad but we’ve grown so much through it all. 2022 was HARD. 2023 already feels more challenging but I also feel stronger than ever. We will get through it, we will learn and become more resilient and thankfully, we will get through it together, even if we are physically apart. Love you darling. Thanks for sharing the burden and beauty of life with me this off-season. @theericoakley

This is Hershey. She’s our least athletic cat shown here. I also have a video in the archive where she failed at the same task a few months ago. Not the most nimble cat out there. #catsofinstagram #cats #funny

This is a lesson in life. It’s not just about pottery, it’s about how you can’t expect to be good at something without first being bad at it and falling on your face in front of people first. Failing is learning. Failing is progress. Failing is necessary and it means that you are challenging yourself. So you. If you’ve failed at something recently, weather it’s making pots or wiping out on a bike,  good job! What did you learn? Now get back up and let’s try again. #Ceramics #pottery #art #homepotterystudio #pottersofinstagram #clay #loveinpottery #handmade #diy #oddlysatisfying #failure #fail #failwithgrwce #failingislearning

Here are some photos from just the last week. It’s been jam packed with meetings and productivity but I’m feeling good (though exhausted). Costa Rica was beautiful, warm, fun and full of great talks, walks and views. (Oh and a new tattoo!) I’ll make a separate post for that adventure. I’m surprisingly happy to be home but mostly because I am working like a fiend on @whalesacs, the garden @sunandsoilgardens and the house, as well as catching up with some people and doing my self work/routine every day too. My mom arrives this evening! What an adventure life can be. I feel scattered and yet so happy with the things I’m doing. I’m so thankful for my brain space since doing @itsnicolebrennan the Liberation Code. I REALLY like the new me and it’s only getting better. #happy #friendship #flowertattoo #sidehandtattoo #larkspurtattoo #flowers

Look at this BEAUTIFUL Albo monstera. This was a dream plant for awhile until we finally got one! It’s so pretty and it started as one single leaf! She really brightens up my plant shelf in my office and brings me so much joy. #plant #planty #albomonstera #albo #varigatedmonstera #plantlover

My beautiful morning. 
Morning pages- learning about myself, my mind, my soul, every morning. Continuing to check in and make sure I’m balanced and what I’m doing aligns with who I am.
Hershey- the most compassionate animal I’ve ever met. Unconditional love at its finest. My heart.
Yoga- checking in with my body and slowing my breathing, giving my body what it needs so I can live longer, better and do more physical activity in the garden, on the course, wherever.
Coffee- warms me from the inside out. Tastes like nature that I LOVE and makes me feel at home no matter where I am on the planet.
 
I am so thankful for who and what I have in my life. I’m so thankful for how I’m changing, how I’m showing up for the people around me and for myself. I’m so thankful to be discovering who I am behind fear, embarrassment, my own negativity bias. Removing those things from my life is revealing a person I didn’t know could exist and I love her so fully. She’s more of a badass than I could have hoped for. 🤗 #mindfulness #morningpages #hope #dream #loveyourself

I’ll be honest, I really haven’t wanted to post photos of myself publicly lately. I’m going through something interesting where I really dislike how I look in every photo, and in the mirror. Considering I’ve gained unmeasurable amounts of inner confidence, this is really interesting to me. Anyways, despite my better judgement, here are some photos from the last 2 weeks. I’ve been having a blast with friends, in the garden and clay, and with Eric too. Things have been really good and positive at home, with work and mentally. I’m so grateful for the people in my life that let me be ME and that bring out a side of me I am proud of and confident in. I truly am lucky.

Enjoying our first day vending at Music City Open. A lot has changed since I was last out vending, and also a lot has stayed the same. It’s a cold one here but being surrounded by friends and disc golf sure makes my heart warm.

I’m sure y’all are sick of hearing about it… but I’m now finishing my FOURTH time watching The Sandman Netflix… so if you haven’t watched it yet… what are you doing with your lives?! Watch it and then message me so I have someone to geek out with. 😂 
I’m also reading the comics that Eric kindly gifted me.

I wanted to share a few things that I got out of the kiln yesterday. I’m REALLY enjoying pottery right now. Like a LOT. I’ve had a lot of commissioned pieces which I’m learning I REALLY enjoy- they have direction and a home! I’m actually really enjoying most of what I’m up to every day with a few exceptions (which I’m determined to fix). I’ve felt a bit nonexistent online as of late. I’ve put time and energy into a few things that haven’t panned out as I expected and have definitely felt pretty discouraged about those but I’m going to work through it and come out even better. I leave for Mexico tomorrow which will be a much needed break from the daily grind stuff that isn’t so fun. I’ll miss my cats and my pots and plants though.

I haven’t been posting much lately but I’ve been traveling like crazy and busy the few days I’ve been home, catching up and getting ready to leave again. I’ve had the pleasure of visiting Puerto Vallarta with my family, followed by a trip with my beautiful lady friends for their bachelorette trip to Lake Tahoe. I am so thankful for the people in my life. I feel so loved and supported especially during a very trying time for me. I even got to see my husband for a bit, a VERY welcomed surprise and much needed time. I am happy to be home with the cats, garden and pottery to refocus, and make progress on some things that have taken a back seat. 

📸Shout out to @alyssavanlanen for making me look cute in the first 3 photos, and just taking amazing photos!!

I would gladly take my emotional, angsty, dramatic young days over all the ￼adult crap that seems to be never ending right now.  Bring back emo days when “overthinking” was pretty much my only struggle.

I got a handful of pieces back, including a bunch of lil Whales that I’m not quite going to show you yet! But there are 2 of these super cool incense burners that I absolutely LOVE. Today I am sharing with you the color yellow. Every photo has a bit of that color, one of my very favorites right now. 
I haven’t been posting ACTUAL posts lately, maybe I’ve been feeling like what I’m doing isn’t worth sharing in a “permanent” way. I still post stories fairly often.
It’s interesting being at home so much, it sometimes makes life seem a little insignificant, or I get too wrapped up in myself and my surroundings, it’s hard to even think about the outside world. As most of you probably know my life is mostly plants, pottery, friends and kitties. Not all bad. #yellow #color #garden #sunflower #colortheme

Fun fact. I used to be in color guard in high school, and had the pleasure of teaching/choreographing and assisting 2 colorguard groups after I graduated - alongside my fellow passionate twirler Holly Anez. 
We are going to Bonaroo to teach some disc golf and of course absorb some music, and I thought this would be a great way to represent disc golf (I put a disc golf basket on the flag) while also giving me something fun to do, AND something tall like this helps us find our group in the crowd- it’s called a totem at Hulaween. 
I am REALLY rusty with my moves but it’s amazing how many pieces I remember and can perform just from muscle memory, you’d have no idea it’s been 16 years since I’ve been in colorguard. 
P.s. I think the pole I bought is a little too long. I haven’t really gotten taller since high school 😂😂 #colorguard #discgolf #bonaroo #totem #flag #toomanyhobbies

I don’t have NEARLY enough photos from @bonnaroo but that’s because I was so THERE and present and taking in as much of my surroundings as possible. Thanks to Bonnaroo, @ppierce29190 and @discraftdiscgolf for having DISC GOLF at Bonnaroo. It was such an amazing and exciting experience bringing disc golf to a place it’s never been before. We felt so much love, and had a huge turnout for Paige’s DG exhibition. I would encourage every person here to try and sneak disc golf into other parts of your life that you wouldn’t expect it to be popular. 
As for Bonnaroo itself, highlights were Odesza- our group was on an another level for their set. For not knowing their music I was enthralled. @paramore back in my emo days, people always called me Hailey Williams, an honor. Turns out she’s my age and has been rocking since we were like 14. She’s a total badass,  an inspiration and owned that stage like it was her kingdom. I’m feeling quite nostalgic. We saw so many other bands I loved moving and dancing too and I also had a huge victory of boundaries last week that served me so well. Took time for myself when needed and enjoyed almost every minute because of that. I’m thankful for these beautiful friends of mine that I am so lucky to spend a ridiculous amount of time with, being truly myself, whatever that looks like for the day. Festivals allow for that in a way that’s hard to find elsewhere, I’m happy to have felt it in a group of 80,000 other humans that aren’t judging, objectifying and harassing. Just love. #bonnaroo #bonnaroo2023 #paigepiercediscgolf #paigepierce

Spending my birthday with @amerika71262 in Denver! This last minute trip has been SO fulfilling and I still have so much more time. So thankful for the people in my life and the opportunities I have, just being able to be here is amazing. More to come.

Tossing the new Dune midrange at a new course with new friends in Denver! This is penny 😜 Denver has been so fun. Full of business, disc golf, friends, drinks, adventures, very little sleep, plants and actually some MAJOR journaling because my head has been full of dreams, future dreams and past dreams I let die. I learn so much when I travel. It’s great but it can also challenging, but I’m up for the challenge. 
Great news, we will have a VLOG for this trip! #coloradodiscgolf #discgolf #trashpanda #discgolflife

Denver was a BLAST. I’m seriously so thankful I was able to go, and that @amerika71262 was there, and that I got to spend so much time with the @trashpandadiscgolf team. They’re doing some really incredible things over there, it’s contagious. Let’s all follow suite and help grow the sport sustainably, just changing one little habit can make a huge difference over time, maybe start by throwing recycled plastic? 
I’m home for a little over a week before I leave for another 3.5 weeks in Europe and the UK, and although I’m tired, I am also motivated, inspired and excited about a few projects I think I’ve been too scared to start, but didn’t realize that is what was holding me back. So I guess here’s to the future, one full of focus, conscious decision making, and running ahead with confidence.
Just a little live garden tour. 🥰

One of my favorite pieces I’ve gotten back. And one of the last I’ll get for awhile. It’s a little tea bag container!! I still need to make a bunch of tea to go in it. Is it cute?? Unfortunately with 2 separate big trips coming up, ceramics are going to have to take a back seat for a couple months. I’m sad, but I’ll make up for it with Finnish and British and Scottish adventures. ##ceramics #pottery #art #homepotterystudio #pottersofinstagram #clay #loveinpottery #handmade #diy #teaset
Can’t. I meant I CANT HELP IT… Don’t mind her angry face. That’s just how she always looks. PLEASE make sure you’re subscribed to Whalepants on YouTube cause we’re about to drop a VOOGGGGGG!

What I see from my new yoga space. It’s not just my yoga space it is the most relaxing space I’ve ever created for myself. It took around 60 hours (cleaning, painting, creating a massive curtain, planning, hanging plants, etc., but it’s such a peaceful environment. With Florida’s summer heat and humidity you’d think I wouldn’t spend time outside but it’s so inviting, it calls to me every morning before it gets too hot. I am so thankful for my home and the space and the creativity I’ve gathered through my travels to dream up such a space. Do you have a sacred spot in your house that you’ve made to suit YOU? P.s. my dream is to host tea parties here. #yoga #porch #plants #sacredspace #yogaroom #dreamporch

I’m leaving for Finland tomorrow! Wow it’s finally here! I am very excited to go back to Finland and the UK, visiting some friends I met last year and hopefully making new friends too! If you’re at the European Open, come say Hi!

I’m sorry I haven’t posted while in Finland!!! You can follow my stories, I post there a lot. 🥰 But here is a beautiful photo of this amazing course on Åland Island, there’s a rainbow if you look closely 🌈. Also, @theericoakley hit the basket on his tee shot right after this photo  was taken, you’ll have to watch the VLOG to see though! Spending our final day on the island, taking a 1 am ferry to Stockholm tonight, then Eric heads home, and I head to the UK for a couple weeks 🇬🇧. Feeling so thankful for what Disc Golf has given us over the years. Adventure, travel, amazing humans, knowledge, culture, understanding, connection. I feel warm and fuzzy as I type this. #ålandopen #discgolffinland #discgolfsweden #swedishdiscgolfprotour #dgpt #discgolf #birdiefuelcoffee #whalesacs @whalesacs @swedishdiscgolfprotour

York!!! This place is OLDE! (The last picture is Edinburgh ).
I’ve honestly spent so little time “relaxing” it’s been completely off my mind to share my trip here but do check my stories daily. 
London, Edinburgh and York have been amazing. So much history, and also for me, I’m a movie nerd and I’ve visited a lot of filming locations which gives me a certain type of excitement that’s hard to explain and has also brought me to some unexpected beautiful places. 
Tomorrow is Bath and Bristol, then Wales, some disc golf with friends and Cheddar Gorge, then I’m heading home. What a packed trip but my learning part of me brain is so freaking happy and full. #travel #uk #Edinburgh #york #yorkengland

5 Years married to my best friend. Woah. I’m so thankful to celebrate our love together surrounded by friends and family in Vermont. Our relationship wouldn’t be what it is without all the other people who have supported us throughout the years. Things have not always been easy, in fact they’ve been very difficult sometimes, including now. But through conversations, open minds and hearts and so much love, we’ve made it here, so happy to live in each others company, living for ourselves AND for each other. I’m so thankful for all the lessons we’ve learned along the way that has made us both better people.
Here’s to many more years, with each other, surrounded by amazing humans that help fuel our crazy/ridiculous life together. 
📸 photo: my amazing friend @alyssavanlanen @alyssavanlanenimages

I’ve had SUCH an incredible week with friends so far. A lot of these humans I met online during the pandemic 3 years ago, the others through travel with disc golf. To say I’m thankful for these people is such an understatement. They have all impacted me in different and significant ways, getting me through hard times and offering so many laughs and good times. To be together in one place with so many of our discord people, and joining my in person life with my online life has been SO FREAKING FUN. More adventures to come, and so many people aren’t pictured here. Thank you for the memories.

This is so silly, I had to share. It’s compost and manure, I’ve put so much energy into the garden this year, but my soil is pretty depleted, this will help IMMENSELY and allow me to plant anywhere and everywhere I like! #gardening #florist #smallbusiness

Having a blast at USDGC already. I don’t know if it’s just the amazing space my brain has been in, but I’m just FEELING the good vibes out here!! Hulaween. 
Music you feel inside your bones and soul. Connections with other humans that fills your heart. 
Art and beauty in every corner. 
Humans who emit love, acceptance and kindness unlike anything I’ve every experienced elsewhere. 

It’s such a special place that shows you what society COULD be like. Peaceful and caring and free.
Last year Hulaween was my first ever music festival (other than like… warped tour lol) and it has changed me. It’s really hard to describe the full effect that this place has but I can tell you I am a better person because of it. 
It’s hard to want to leave a world like that but I’m thankful for my friends that also experience it and bring that out into the outside world with them. That is a unique bond. And I am so grateful. @hulaweenfl
